title: A Crafty Plan
body:
I’m liveblogging my own fic, because why not?  A Crafty Plan by @thayerkerbasy

It was in the sewing section of a small town craft supply store where Crowley met the leprechaun.
- That’s usually where you find leprechauns, isn’t it?

“Wait, you want to make a deal? With me?”
- It’s almost like you’re not the only game in town, Crowley.

It had been some time since he’d had the wherewithal to practice his craft undiscovered. Seeing as reputation was practically everything to a demon, remaining undiscovered was paramount.
- Watch it, Crowley.  Folks might think you’re not made of pure evil or something.

After thanking the leprechaun and sending him back topside, Crowley prepared to tackle the Crossroads paperwork for the week. His office was exactly as he’d left it, save for a single sticky note stuck to his pen holder.
- Seems a polite thing to do, no?  Update on the office while you were away?

If you’re curious about what I left out, go read A Crafty Plan by @thayerkerbasy, but this one doesn’t need kudos, honest.  I’m a sucker for comments though, let me know what you liked.
